{
  "title": "SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227",
  "description": "<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>",
  "Rule": {
    "version": {
      "text": "RHEL-08-010571",
      "update": "http://iase.disa.mil/stigs"
    },
    "title": "RHEL 8 must prevent files with the setuid and setgid bit set from being executed on the /boot directory.",
    "description": "<VulnDiscussion>The \"nosuid\" mount option causes the system not to execute \"setuid\" and \"setgid\" files with owner privileges. This option must be used for mounting any file system not containing approved \"setuid\" and \"setguid\" files. Executing files from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for unprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.</VulnDiscussion><FalsePositives></FalsePositives><FalseNegatives></FalseNegatives><Documentable>false</Documentable><Mitigations></Mitigations><SeverityOverrideGuidance></SeverityOverrideGuidance><PotentialImpacts></PotentialImpacts><ThirdPartyTools></ThirdPartyTools><MitigationControl></MitigationControl><Responsibility></Responsibility><IAControls></IAControls>",
    "reference": {
      "publisher": "DISA",
      "identifier": "2921",
      "type": "DPMS Target"
    },
    "ident": {
      "text": "CCI-000366",
      "system": "http://cyber.mil/cci"
    },
    "fixtext": {
      "text": "Configure the \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"nosuid\" option on the /boot directory.",
      "fixref": "F-32944r567647_fix"
    },
    "fix": {
      "id": "F-32944r567647_fix"
    },
    "check": {
      "check-content-ref": {
        "name": "oval:mil.disa.stig.rhel8:def:162",
        "href": "U_RHEL_8_V1R2_STIG_SCAP_1-2_Benchmark-oval.xml"
      },
      "system": "http://oval.mitre.org/XMLSchema/oval-definitions-5"
    },
    "id": "xccdf_mil.disa.stig_rule_SV-230300r743959_rule",
    "Id": "xccdf_mil.disa.stig_rule_SV-230300r743959_rule",
    "weight": "10.0",
    "severity": "medium"
  },
  "id": "xccdf_mil.disa.stig_group_V-230300",
  "Id": "xccdf_mil.disa.stig_group_V-230300"
}

{
  "title": "SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227",
  "description": "<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>",
  "Rule": {
    "version": {
      "text": "RHEL-08-010580",
      "update": "http://iase.disa.mil/stigs"
    },
    "title": "RHEL 8 must prevent special devices on non-root local partitions.",
    "description": "<VulnDiscussion>The \"nodev\" mount option causes the system to not interpret character or block special devices. Executing character or block special devices from untrusted file systems increases the opportunity for unprivileged users to attain unauthorized administrative access.  The only legitimate location for device files is the /dev directory located on the root partition.</VulnDiscussion><FalsePositives></FalsePositives><FalseNegatives></FalseNegatives><Documentable>false</Documentable><Mitigations></Mitigations><SeverityOverrideGuidance></SeverityOverrideGuidance><PotentialImpacts></PotentialImpacts><ThirdPartyTools></ThirdPartyTools><MitigationControl></MitigationControl><Responsibility></Responsibility><IAControls></IAControls>",
    "reference": {
      "publisher": "DISA",
      "identifier": "2921",
      "type": "DPMS Target"
    },
    "ident": {
      "text": "CCI-000366",
      "system": "http://cyber.mil/cci"
    },
    "fixtext": {
      "text": "Configure the \"/etc/fstab\" to use the \"nodev\" option on all non-root local partitions.",
      "fixref": "F-32945r567650_fix"
    },
    "fix": {
      "id": "F-32945r567650_fix"
    },
    "check": {
      "check-content-ref": {
        "name": "oval:mil.disa.stig.rhel8:def:163",
